Over here!

280
00:18:06,034 --> 00:18:06,966
Clement?

281
00:18:07,002 --> 00:18:10,036
Serena, Bonnie,
this is incredible!

282
00:18:10,072 --> 00:18:13,873
This is the Azoth Kingdom!

283
00:18:13,909 --> 00:18:16,843
The Azoth Kingdom?

284
00:18:16,878 --> 00:18:18,878
It's an ultra-mechanized city.

285
00:18:18,914 --> 00:18:20,880
We'll find the great
scientist Nicola

286
00:18:20,916 --> 00:18:22,882
using arcane science and art.

287
00:18:22,918 --> 00:18:23,883
[LAUGHING]

288
00:18:23,919 --> 00:18:26,619
Mechanized?

289
00:18:26,655 --> 00:18:27,921
Nicola was a genius.

290
00:18:27,956 --> 00:18:30,990
He's truly one of
my all-time idols.

291
00:18:31,026 --> 00:18:33,893
He used Pokemon
skills as inspiration

292
00:18:33,929 --> 00:18:35,795
for his many inventions.

293
00:18:35,831 --> 00:18:38,598
Truly a great man.

294
00:18:38,633 --> 00:18:39,065
[INAUDIBLE].

295
00:18:44,072 --> 00:18:47,006
[INAUDIBLE].

296
00:18:47,042 --> 00:18:49,976
[GRUNTING]

297
00:18:50,011 --> 00:18:51,644
[GASPING]

298
00:18:52,681 --> 00:18:55,081
Huh?

299
00:18:55,117 --> 00:18:56,082
[CHUCKLE]

300
00:18:56,118 --> 00:18:57,884
Pikaboo.

301
00:18:57,919 --> 00:18:58,852
[CHUCKLE]

302
00:19:01,089 --> 00:19:03,056
[STOMPING]

303
00:19:03,091 --> 00:19:04,057
[GRUNT]

304
00:19:07,863 --> 00:19:08,995
[ROBOT NOISES]

305
00:19:09,030 --> 00:19:12,899
For you, I would walk
through fire and water.

306
00:19:12,934 --> 00:19:14,601
Pika-pi!

307
00:19:14,636 --> 00:19:16,002
Pikachu!

308
00:19:16,037 --> 00:19:17,904
[ROBOT NOISES]

309
00:19:17,939 --> 00:19:20,607
So they call you
Volcanion, don't they?

310
00:19:20,642 --> 00:19:23,576
Mm, and what do they do?

311
00:19:23,612 --> 00:19:24,043
[ROBOT NOISES]

312
00:19:26,982 --> 00:19:31,017
Magearna, you really are
a one-of-a-kind Pokemon.

313
00:19:31,052 --> 00:19:31,985
Pika.

314
00:19:32,020 --> 00:19:33,987
Hahaha.

315
00:19:34,022 --> 00:19:35,655
Magearna, everything OK?

316
00:19:35,690 --> 00:19:36,823
[ROBOT NOISE]

317
00:19:36,858 --> 00:19:39,826
My name's Ash, And
this is my pal Pikachu.

318
00:19:39,861 --> 00:19:40,994
Pika, Pikachu.

319
00:19:41,029 --> 00:19:41,995
[ROBOT NOISE]

320
00:19:42,030 --> 00:19:43,062
[GRUNT]

321
00:19:43,098 --> 00:19:44,898
It's nice to meet you too.

322
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:45,865
[GRUNT]

323
00:19:45,901 --> 00:19:48,668
Don't touch it!

324
00:19:48,703 --> 00:19:49,669
[BELL DINGS]

325
00:19:50,739 --> 00:19:51,671
Pika.

326
00:19:59,981 --> 00:20:01,881
Hey, what are you doing?

327
00:20:01,917 --> 00:20:03,950
I can't blast
anything without water.

328
00:20:03,985 --> 00:20:04,984
You can't?

329
00:20:05,020 --> 00:20:05,952
Pika.

330
00:20:08,690 --> 00:20:09,756
Don't worry.

331
00:20:09,791 --> 00:20:12,859
If those guys show up again,
we'll chase them away.

332
00:20:12,894 --> 00:20:15,962
I don't from humans.

333
00:20:15,997 --> 00:20:16,930
Pikachu.

334
00:20:16,965 --> 00:20:18,932
Stay out of this,
electric nuisance.

335
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:19,999
Pika.

336
00:20:20,035 --> 00:20:20,934
Pika-eh-kachu!

337
00:20:23,872 --> 00:20:24,704
Listen up.

338
00:20:24,739 --> 00:20:26,673
I'll tell you just one.

339
00:20:26,708 --> 00:20:29,943
I will never trust humans.

340
00:20:29,978 --> 00:20:32,846
To Pokemon like you
that cozy up to humans,

341
00:20:32,881 --> 00:20:34,981
I don't trust them either.

342
00:20:35,016 --> 00:20:36,883
Pika, Pika.

343
00:20:36,918 --> 00:20:37,951
What, Pipsqueak?

344
00:20:37,986 --> 00:20:40,954
What to fight?

345
00:20:40,989 --> 00:20:41,921
Come on.

346
00:20:41,957 --> 00:20:43,857
Everybody just calm down now.

347
00:20:43,892 --> 00:20:44,858
[GRUMBLE]

348
00:20:44,893 --> 00:20:46,059
[ROBOT NOISES]

349
00:20:47,896 --> 00:20:48,862
Pik.

350
00:20:48,897 --> 00:20:50,697
Pika.

351
00:20:50,732 --> 00:20:51,998
We found them!

352
00:20:52,033 --> 00:20:54,934
[PANTING] Ash!

353
00:20:54,970 --> 00:20:56,903
everyone!

354
00:20:56,938 --> 00:20:57,904
Huh?

355
00:20:57,939 --> 00:21:01,074
[ROBOT NOISE]

356
00:21:01,109 --> 00:21:02,942
JARVIS: I see.

357
00:21:02,978 --> 00:21:06,613
You say that you know
that young boy trainer.

358
00:21:06,648 --> 00:21:08,014
Boy, do we ever.

359
00:21:08,049 --> 00:21:09,949
Quite-- for a very long time.

360
00:21:09,985 --> 00:21:10,917
Too long.

361
00:21:10,952 --> 00:21:11,985
You have no idea.

362
00:21:12,020 --> 00:21:14,020
And you call
yourselves Team Rocket.

363
00:21:14,055 --> 00:21:15,088
I'll need more information.

364
00:21:15,123 --> 00:21:16,723
TOGETHER: More?

365
00:21:16,758 --> 00:21:17,690
Sure!

366
00:21:21,062 --> 00:21:23,696
Just meeting the
mythical Pokemon Volcanion

367
00:21:23,732 --> 00:21:24,931
would've been amazing.

368
00:21:24,966 --> 00:21:28,701
But to actually meet Nicola's
greatest creation of all time?

369
00:21:28,737 --> 00:21:30,003
I'm honored!

370
00:21:30,038 --> 00:21:31,004
[ROBOT NOISE]

371
00:21:31,039 --> 00:21:31,971
Mm.

372
00:21:32,007 --> 00:21:32,972
[CRACKLE]

373
00:21:33,008 --> 00:21:35,675
Huh?

374
00:21:35,710 --> 00:21:36,709
It's never coming off.

375
00:21:36,745 --> 00:21:37,677
Pika.

376
00:21:37,712 --> 00:21:40,046
You humans are useless.

377
00:21:40,081 --> 00:21:41,047
That's not nice.

378
00:21:41,082 --> 00:21:42,882
[INAUDIBLE].

379
00:21:42,918 --> 00:21:43,716
I'm sorry.

380
00:21:43,752 --> 00:21:44,918
Please forgive me.

381
00:21:44,953 --> 00:21:45,952
Huh?

382
00:21:45,987 --> 00:21:46,920
[GASP]

383
00:21:46,955 --> 00:21:49,889
[ROBOT NOISES]

384
00:21:49,925 --> 00:21:52,692
[DELIGHTED GASP]

385
00:21:52,727 --> 00:21:54,060
Thank you, Magearna.

386
00:21:54,095 --> 00:21:55,929
You're a Pokemon treasure.

387
00:21:55,964 --> 00:21:57,130
Don't touch it!

388
00:21:57,165 --> 00:21:58,131
Huh?

389
00:21:58,166 --> 00:21:59,666
Look out!

390
00:21:59,701 --> 00:22:00,099
Wah!

391
00:22:00,135 --> 00:22:02,068
Pika!

392
00:22:02,103 --> 00:22:04,037
[GROANING]

393
00:22:06,174 --> 00:22:07,774
Why me?

394
00:22:07,809 --> 00:22:08,741
Ugh.

395
00:22:08,777 --> 00:22:09,742
(SADLY) Pika.

396
00:22:09,778 --> 00:22:10,710
Hi, there!

397
00:22:10,745 --> 00:22:11,744
We're back!

398
00:22:11,780 --> 00:22:12,879
Huh?

399
00:22:12,914 --> 00:22:13,746
Magearna?

400
00:22:17,686 --> 00:22:18,918
[ROBOT NOISE]

401
00:22:18,954 --> 00:22:19,919
[AMAZED GASPS]

402
00:22:19,988 --> 00:22:20,920
Amazing!

403
00:22:20,956 --> 00:22:22,088
Incredible!

404
00:22:22,123 --> 00:22:23,089
[LAUGHING]

405
00:22:23,124 --> 00:22:24,757
Kind of like a Poke Ball.

406
00:22:24,793 --> 00:22:26,059
- Pikachu.
- Ash?

407
00:22:26,094 --> 00:22:27,060
Huh?

408
00:22:27,095 --> 00:22:28,194
Tada!

409
00:22:28,229 --> 00:22:31,998
Since your clothes are a
mess, how about you try these?

410
00:22:32,033 --> 00:22:34,634
Hmm.

411
00:22:34,669 --> 00:22:37,070
Uh-- hmm.

412
00:22:37,105 --> 00:22:39,005
Wow, you look great.

413
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:39,939
Really?

414
00:22:39,975 --> 00:22:41,975
Pikachu, Magearna, do I?

415
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:43,643
Pika-Pika!

416
00:22:43,678 --> 00:22:45,645
[EXCITED ROBOT NOISE]

417
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:47,914
Stop it, Magearna.

418
00:22:47,949 --> 00:22:49,782
Don't get involved
with these humans.

419
00:22:49,818 --> 00:22:53,052
[ROBOT NOISES]

420
00:22:53,088 --> 00:22:54,721
I refuse.

421
00:22:54,756 --> 00:22:55,788
[ROBOT NOISES]

422
00:22:55,824 --> 00:22:56,756
Leave me alone!

423
00:22:56,791 --> 00:22:58,658
[ROBOT NOISES]

424
00:23:00,695 --> 00:23:01,661
[POOF]

425
00:23:01,696 --> 00:23:02,929
[GASP]

426
00:23:06,968 --> 00:23:09,769
[GEARING UP TO SNEEZE]

427
00:23:10,772 --> 00:23:12,071
[ROARING]

428
00:23:12,107 --> 00:23:13,039
Choo!

429
00:23:17,746 --> 00:23:18,845
[GRUMBLE]

430
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:21,681
Hey, I told you to
quit it, didn't I?

431
00:23:24,419 --> 00:23:24,917
OK, fine.

432
00:23:24,953 --> 00:23:26,719
I'll doing my best.

433
00:23:26,788 --> 00:23:29,422
[ROBOT NOISES]

434
00:23:30,759 --> 00:23:31,724
[SPLASH]

435
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:32,592
Aah!

436
00:23:32,627 --> 00:23:33,526
Magearna!

437
00:23:36,531 --> 00:23:38,464
[ALL GRUNTING]

438
00:23:42,537 --> 00:23:43,803
Are you all right?

439
00:23:43,838 --> 00:23:46,506
[ROBOT NOISES]

440
00:23:49,477 --> 00:23:50,710
Magearna, you're soaking wet.

441
00:23:50,745 --> 00:23:53,479
We'll get you all dried up.

442
00:23:53,515 --> 00:23:54,714
[ROBOT NOISES]

443
00:23:54,783 --> 00:23:56,516
Well, that's a relief.

444
00:23:56,551 --> 00:23:58,785
Though you've got to
admit, Magearna's heavy.

445
00:23:58,820 --> 00:24:00,520
[ROBOT NOISES]

446
00:24:01,489 --> 00:24:02,455
Gearna?

447
00:24:02,490 --> 00:24:03,456
Pika?

448
00:24:03,491 --> 00:24:06,726
It looks embarrassed.

449
00:24:06,761 --> 00:24:07,860
Because it fell?

450
00:24:07,896 --> 00:24:11,431
I don't like Magearna
likes being called heavy.

451
00:24:11,466 --> 00:24:12,765
You're kidding.

452
00:24:12,801 --> 00:24:15,435
Of course it
doesn't like that.

453
00:24:15,470 --> 00:24:16,769
[GASP]

454
00:24:16,805 --> 00:24:18,504
I'm so very sorry.

455
00:24:18,540 --> 00:24:19,505
Please forgive me.

456
00:24:19,541 --> 00:24:21,707
Clemont means
well, but he just

457
00:24:21,743 --> 00:24:23,509
doesn't understand some things.

458
00:24:23,545 --> 00:24:24,544
[GIGGLE]

459
00:24:24,579 --> 00:24:25,478
We should go.

460
00:24:25,513 --> 00:24:26,579
The sun is setting.

461
00:24:26,614 --> 00:24:28,781
[ROBOT NOISES]

462
00:24:32,420 --> 00:24:34,554
No.

463
00:24:34,589 --> 00:24:37,824
I said, no!

464
00:24:37,859 --> 00:24:41,727
I won't bring humans along.

465
00:24:41,763 --> 00:24:43,696
Hey, where you going?

466
00:24:43,731 --> 00:24:46,699
Come back!

467
00:24:46,734 --> 00:24:47,700
Huh?

468
00:24:47,735 --> 00:24:50,403
Not again.

469
00:24:50,438 --> 00:24:51,871
[YELLING]

470
00:24:53,641 --> 00:24:54,574
Pika-pi!

471
00:24:56,911 --> 00:24:57,844
Huh?

472
00:24:57,879 --> 00:25:00,446
[MURMURING]

473
00:25:02,517 --> 00:25:05,885
We need to get away right now.

474
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:08,421
[ROBOT NOISES]

475
00:25:08,456 --> 00:25:09,755
Get moving, or I'll
leave you behind.

476
00:25:20,635 --> 00:25:22,468
Raleigh, wait.

477
00:25:22,504 --> 00:25:23,436
Chymia!

478
00:25:23,471 --> 00:25:24,470
What is it?

479
00:25:24,506 --> 00:25:26,839
I saw you standing up
on the tower wall before.

480
00:25:26,875 --> 00:25:29,475
And you were with Alva, as well.

481
00:25:29,511 --> 00:25:30,476
What were you up to?

482
00:25:30,512 --> 00:25:32,612
A scientific investigation.

483
00:25:32,647 --> 00:25:34,614
Many of the amazing
machines built by Nicola

484
00:25:34,649 --> 00:25:36,582
are operating even now.

485
00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:37,817
Oh, is that all?

486
00:25:37,852 --> 00:25:39,385
Listen to me.

487
00:25:39,420 --> 00:25:41,587
If you really want to
learn, look to the future,

488
00:25:41,623 --> 00:25:42,822
not just to the past.

489
00:25:42,857 --> 00:25:43,923
The future?

490
00:25:43,958 --> 00:25:46,425
To do that, you need to
learn about the past, see?

491
00:25:50,431 --> 00:25:52,632
Father is worried
about you, as well.

492
00:25:52,667 --> 00:25:55,535
Alva was with me, so
there was no need to worry.

493
00:25:55,570 --> 00:25:57,870
But that's why he's worried.

494
00:25:57,906 --> 00:25:59,639
Now, you know that
father trusts Alva

495
00:25:59,674 --> 00:26:01,774
completely, just like I do.

496
00:26:01,809 --> 00:26:07,446
He thinks a lot more about our
kingdom's future than you do.

497
00:26:07,482 --> 00:26:10,616
So if you'll please
excuse me, I have to go.

498
00:26:21,596 --> 00:26:23,362
1, 2--

499
00:26:23,398 --> 00:26:24,564
BOTH: Ta-da!

500
00:26:24,599 --> 00:26:25,531
Whoa!

501
00:26:25,567 --> 00:26:28,568
Isn't it cute, Volcanion?

502
00:26:28,603 --> 00:26:30,803
[BLOOPING]

503
00:26:33,808 --> 00:26:35,408
[SIGH]

504
00:26:38,580 --> 00:26:40,813
Huh?

505
00:26:40,848 --> 00:26:42,782
Well, that went over well.

506
00:26:42,817 --> 00:26:44,417
Maybe it's shy.

507
00:26:44,452 --> 00:26:45,384
Could be.

508
00:26:45,420 --> 00:26:46,452
Right, Magearna?

509
00:26:46,487 --> 00:26:48,521
[BEEPING]

510
00:26:48,556 --> 00:26:49,855
Getting friendly, aren't they?

511
00:26:49,891 --> 00:26:51,624
Sure are.

512
00:26:51,659 --> 00:26:54,794
Since we're stuck together
now, might as well have fun.

513
00:26:54,829 --> 00:26:56,596
- I agree.
- Nonsense.

514
00:26:56,631 --> 00:26:58,397
I just want to
get away from you.

515
00:26:58,433 --> 00:27:00,499
Nothing good comes from
interacting with humans.

516
00:27:00,535 --> 00:27:01,434
Huh?

517
00:27:01,469 --> 00:27:02,802
You fell out of the
sky with these bands.

518
00:27:02,837 --> 00:27:03,669
Remember?

519
00:27:03,705 --> 00:27:05,871
Look, humans
made these things.

520
00:27:05,907 --> 00:27:07,640
Well, it sure wasn't us.

521
00:27:07,675 --> 00:27:09,508
All humans are the same.

522
00:27:09,544 --> 00:27:10,476
Pika!

523
00:27:14,582 --> 00:27:15,615
Hey, you.

524
00:27:15,650 --> 00:27:18,484
What are you doing
hanging around like that?

525
00:27:18,519 --> 00:27:21,487
Get your filthy
human hands off me.

526
00:27:21,522 --> 00:27:22,488
No, I won't!

527
00:27:22,523 --> 00:27:23,489
Cut it out, I said.

528
00:27:23,524 --> 00:27:24,790
No, you first!

529
00:27:24,826 --> 00:27:26,792
I'll blast you off.

530
00:27:35,870 --> 00:27:36,802
Agh.

531
00:27:40,642 --> 00:27:42,408
JARVIS: If they're
headed somewhere,

532
00:27:42,443 --> 00:27:44,810
it's probably Nebel Plateau.

533
00:27:44,846 --> 00:27:47,546
Oh, the place with the field
of flowers where Magearna was

534
00:27:47,582 --> 00:27:48,514
found.

535
00:27:48,549 --> 00:27:50,516
Yes.

536
00:27:50,551 --> 00:27:53,786
Members of Team Rocket,
please go investigate.

537
00:27:53,821 --> 00:27:55,588
Count on us, sir!

538
00:27:55,623 --> 00:27:57,590
[GIGGLING]

539
00:27:57,625 --> 00:27:59,458
It's all finished!

540
00:27:59,494 --> 00:28:00,393
What is?

541
00:28:00,428 --> 00:28:01,827
Have a look for yourselves.

542
00:28:01,863 --> 00:28:04,530
The future is now,
thanks to science.

543
00:28:09,470 --> 00:28:12,371
I made this protective
suits inspired by moves

544
00:28:12,407 --> 00:28:14,407
like iron defense and protect.

545
00:28:14,442 --> 00:28:15,641
It's called Mr. Iron Defense.

546
00:28:15,677 --> 00:28:16,609
Whoa-ho!

547
00:28:19,447 --> 00:28:21,547
You're protected from
any kind of attack.

548
00:28:23,685 --> 00:28:24,617
Huh?

549
00:28:24,652 --> 00:28:26,452
What do I see?

550
00:28:26,487 --> 00:28:28,354
It looks like a camp fire.

551
00:28:28,389 --> 00:28:30,523
Maybe they're setting
up camp here tonight.

552
00:28:30,558 --> 00:28:32,425
We have to tell Alva.

553
00:28:32,460 --> 00:28:33,392
Wait.

554
00:28:33,428 --> 00:28:35,561
Our real boss is the prince.

555
00:28:35,596 --> 00:28:38,564
Once we can get our hands on
what he wants, we'll be rich.

556
00:28:38,599 --> 00:28:39,632
Brilliant!

557
00:28:39,667 --> 00:28:41,367
And that's rich.

558
00:28:41,402 --> 00:28:42,668
Let's make some dough.

559
00:28:42,704 --> 00:28:45,671
[SNORING]

560
00:28:49,877 --> 00:28:50,710
Huh?

561
00:28:50,745 --> 00:28:52,411
You sensed it, too?

562
00:29:00,688 --> 00:29:01,654
Pika.

563
00:29:01,689 --> 00:29:02,621
Pikachu!

564
00:29:05,493 --> 00:29:06,425
Ah!

565
00:29:06,461 --> 00:29:08,361
Huh?

566
00:29:08,396 --> 00:29:10,529
Uh, Magearna!

567
00:29:10,565 --> 00:29:12,531
[BEEPING]

568
00:29:12,567 --> 00:29:13,632
JAMES: Yoo-hoo!

569
00:29:13,668 --> 00:29:15,601
ALL: Huh?

570
00:29:15,636 --> 00:29:17,570
From now on,
Magearna's our guest.

571
00:29:17,605 --> 00:29:18,571
Team Rocket?

572
00:29:18,606 --> 00:29:20,373
What are you guys doing here?

573
00:29:20,408 --> 00:29:20,940
Huh?

574
00:29:20,975 --> 00:29:22,508
Heracross and Pinsir?

575
00:29:22,543 --> 00:29:24,610
Hey, where are
your normal Pokemon?

576
00:29:24,645 --> 00:29:27,346
We're not your
normal Team Rocket.

577
00:29:27,382 --> 00:29:28,247
Check this out.

578
00:29:28,282 --> 00:29:30,683
TEAM ROCKET: Mega
Wave Team Rocket!

579
00:29:30,718 --> 00:29:31,650
What?

580
00:29:31,719 --> 00:29:33,519
Key Stones!

581
00:29:33,554 --> 00:29:36,522
We joined forces with
the good Prince Raleigh.

582
00:29:36,557 --> 00:29:37,456
No way!

583
00:29:37,492 --> 00:29:38,424
See?

584
00:29:38,459 --> 00:29:39,658
We're Mega Wave Team Rocket!

585
00:29:42,663 --> 00:29:43,562
[GASP]

586
00:29:43,598 --> 00:29:44,563
Pika.

587
00:29:44,599 --> 00:29:45,531
Mega Wave!

588
00:29:55,476 --> 00:29:56,409
[SNARLING]

589
00:29:56,444 --> 00:29:57,576
Mega Evolve?

590
00:29:57,612 --> 00:29:58,544
But how?

591
00:29:58,579 --> 00:30:00,513
To Mega Evolve, there
must be a close bond

592
00:30:00,548 --> 00:30:02,481
between trainer and Pokemon.

593
00:30:02,517 --> 00:30:06,552
It's thanks to what Alva
calls-- er, what was it?

594
00:30:06,587 --> 00:30:07,520
Mm.

595
00:30:07,555 --> 00:30:09,655
Neo arcane science.

596
00:30:09,690 --> 00:30:12,391
With this technology, we
can use Mega Evolution

597
00:30:12,427 --> 00:30:14,393
and we don't need
any stinking bond!

598
00:30:14,429 --> 00:30:15,428
I see.

599
00:30:15,463 --> 00:30:16,695
So Gengar and the others--

600
00:30:16,731 --> 00:30:18,697
[SNARLING]

601
00:30:18,733 --> 00:30:20,466
Gengar!

602
00:30:20,501 --> 00:30:22,401
What about how
the Pokemon feel?

603
00:30:22,437 --> 00:30:24,370
That's not Mega Evolution!

604
00:30:24,405 --> 00:30:26,405
Arcane science was
developed to make

605
00:30:26,441 --> 00:30:27,606
people and Pokemon happy!

606
00:30:27,642 --> 00:30:30,543
You're defaming the
memory of Nicola!

607
00:30:30,578 --> 00:30:31,510
Hey!

608
00:30:31,546 --> 00:30:34,380
We call it neo because
technology passed

609
00:30:34,415 --> 00:30:35,648
through by science, guys.

610
00:30:35,683 --> 00:30:36,582
Now, Heracross!

611
00:30:36,617 --> 00:30:37,550
Pinsir, too!

612
00:30:37,585 --> 00:30:41,353
Turn them into goo!

613
00:30:41,389 --> 00:30:42,455
[SCREAMING]

614
00:30:42,490 --> 00:30:44,657
You, take Magearna
away from here.

615
00:30:44,692 --> 00:30:47,593
I hate relying on humans,
but I have no choice.

616
00:30:47,628 --> 00:30:49,361
Go!

617
00:30:49,397 --> 00:30:50,362
Everyone, do it.

618
00:30:50,398 --> 00:30:51,363
All right.

619
00:30:51,399 --> 00:30:51,797
Let's go, Magearna.

620
00:30:51,833 --> 00:30:54,567
Leave it to us.

621
00:30:54,602 --> 00:30:57,470
Let 'er rip.

622
00:30:57,505 --> 00:30:58,604
Pikachu, use Thunderbolt!

623
00:30:58,639 --> 00:30:59,572
Pikachu!

624
00:31:12,753 --> 00:31:13,686
Get him, Volcanion!

625
00:31:13,721 --> 00:31:15,588
I don't need a cheerleader.

626
00:31:26,834 --> 00:31:27,800
Yes!

627
00:31:27,835 --> 00:31:28,767
Pika.

628
00:31:37,678 --> 00:31:39,445
[SCREAMING]

629
00:31:40,815 --> 00:31:41,780
Success!

630
00:31:41,816 --> 00:31:44,483
It worked like a charm.

631
00:31:44,519 --> 00:31:47,486
Mega Evolution
drew Volcanion away.

632
00:31:47,522 --> 00:31:49,488
[SCREAMING]

633
00:31:49,757 --> 00:31:50,689
Gardevoir.

634
00:31:54,495 --> 00:31:55,461
The nerve!

635
00:32:06,641 --> 00:32:09,608
Gardevoir, Mega Evolve!

636
00:32:09,644 --> 00:32:10,576
Gard!

637
00:32:19,554 --> 00:32:20,586
Gardevoir.

638
00:32:20,621 --> 00:32:22,688
MEOWTH: Now there's a
Mega Gardevoir in my face.

639
00:32:22,723 --> 00:32:24,523
Use Dazzling Gleam!

640
00:32:24,559 --> 00:32:25,491
Gardevoir!

641
00:32:32,733 --> 00:32:35,501
TEAM ROCKET: We're
blasting off again!

642
00:32:35,536 --> 00:32:37,469
[SCREAMING]

643
00:32:44,712 --> 00:32:45,611
Wow!

644
00:32:45,646 --> 00:32:46,579
Nothing.

645
00:32:51,819 --> 00:32:52,785
Pikachu!

646
00:32:52,820 --> 00:32:53,786
PIKACHU: Pika.

647
00:32:53,821 --> 00:32:55,788
Let 'em have it, Volcanion.

648
00:32:55,823 --> 00:32:57,556
Don't blame me
for the results.

649
00:32:57,592 --> 00:32:58,557
Don't worry.

650
00:33:14,709 --> 00:33:15,741
Pika Pika!

651
00:33:15,776 --> 00:33:17,776
Science is so amazing.

652
00:33:17,812 --> 00:33:18,777
Pika?

653
00:33:18,813 --> 00:33:19,745
Huh?

654
00:33:29,557 --> 00:33:31,457
So this is your real power.

655
00:33:31,492 --> 00:33:32,691
Ha.

656
00:33:32,727 --> 00:33:35,494
If I showed you my real power,
it wouldn't be just this.

657
00:33:35,529 --> 00:33:36,829
I've leveled a whole mountain.

658
00:33:36,864 --> 00:33:38,631
Awesome.

659
00:33:38,666 --> 00:33:39,598
Pika?

660
00:33:43,604 --> 00:33:44,770
Hey, Ash!

661
00:33:44,805 --> 00:33:46,805
What exploded?

662
00:33:46,841 --> 00:33:48,774
Hey, guys.

663
00:33:48,809 --> 00:33:49,742
Pika!

664
00:33:49,777 --> 00:33:51,644
Now I've got even more humans.

665
00:33:57,518 --> 00:34:00,819
Magearna, I'm Chymia,
princess of Azoth.

666
00:34:00,855 --> 00:34:03,555
Pleased to meet you.

667
00:34:03,591 --> 00:34:05,791
I'm a descendant of
the Azoth royal family.

668
00:34:05,826 --> 00:34:06,759
Princess?

669
00:34:06,794 --> 00:34:07,693
Whoa.

670
00:34:07,728 --> 00:34:08,727
[BEEPING]

671
00:34:27,581 --> 00:34:29,615
[BEEPING]

672
00:34:29,650 --> 00:34:30,616
[GASP]

673
00:34:30,651 --> 00:34:31,550
Oh, my.

674
00:34:31,585 --> 00:34:32,685
They're beautiful.

675
00:34:32,720 --> 00:34:33,819
Thank you.

676
00:34:33,854 --> 00:34:37,756
Volcanion, you were
protecting Magearna, right?

677
00:34:40,561 --> 00:34:41,493
Hm.

678
00:34:45,249 --> 00:34:46,515
CHYMIA: For the kingdom?

679
00:34:46,550 --> 00:34:48,417
That's what Raleigh said, huh?

680
00:34:48,452 --> 00:34:49,418
SERENA: Right.

681
00:34:49,453 --> 00:34:50,686
One thing's for sure.

682
00:34:50,721 --> 00:34:54,523
Raleigh believes everything that
Alva tells him-- that it's all

683
00:34:54,558 --> 00:34:56,392
for the good of the kingdom.

684
00:34:56,427 --> 00:34:59,428
Does Raleigh really trust
this Alva person that much?

685
00:34:59,463 --> 00:35:00,396
Yes.

686
00:35:03,501 --> 00:35:07,403
Ever since Raleigh was a
boy, he always adored Nicola.

687
00:35:07,438 --> 00:35:10,339
Many times, he would spend
the entire day in his room,

688
00:35:10,374 --> 00:35:15,110
reading old texts and
performing experiments.

689
00:35:15,146 --> 00:35:17,579
And because of that, when he
found out that Councilor Alva

690
00:35:17,615 --> 00:35:20,382
was an arcane
science researcher,

691
00:35:20,418 --> 00:35:23,318
he started to spend more
and more time with him.

692
00:35:27,591 --> 00:35:31,126
So now, since my brother
is involved in this,

693
00:35:31,162 --> 00:35:32,461
that means that I am, too.

694
00:35:35,366 --> 00:35:36,498
[YELLING]

695
00:35:39,303 --> 00:35:40,536
Hey, why don't we
just get on board

696
00:35:40,571 --> 00:35:42,337
the thing they're riding on?

697
00:35:42,373 --> 00:35:44,473
Why would I board
something humans built?

698
00:35:44,508 --> 00:35:47,609
Oh, come on.

699
00:35:47,645 --> 00:35:48,577
Ah!

700
00:35:56,620 --> 00:35:57,553
[GASP]

701
00:35:57,588 --> 00:35:59,488
The princess.

702
00:35:59,523 --> 00:36:01,623
I know.

703
00:36:01,659 --> 00:36:02,624
Dedenne.

704
00:36:02,660 --> 00:36:03,592
Wow!

705
00:36:03,627 --> 00:36:04,560
A field of flowers!

706
00:36:09,567 --> 00:36:12,301
Come to greet us, huh?

707
00:36:12,336 --> 00:36:14,303
[FRANTIC CHIRPING]

708
00:36:14,338 --> 00:36:15,304
What?

709
00:36:15,339 --> 00:36:17,272
[CHIRP]

710
00:36:17,308 --> 00:36:18,474
Ah?

711
00:36:18,509 --> 00:36:19,475
Ah!

712
00:36:19,510 --> 00:36:21,276
Huh?

713
00:36:21,312 --> 00:36:24,146
[CHIRPING]

714
00:36:24,181 --> 00:36:25,147
Up ahead.

715
00:36:25,182 --> 00:36:26,381
Is that Amaura?

716
00:36:31,589 --> 00:36:34,389
Amaura's badly injured.

717
00:36:34,425 --> 00:36:36,525
Hold on.

718
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:37,526
[WHIMPERING]

719
00:36:39,563 --> 00:36:40,496
Hang in there.

720
00:36:44,435 --> 00:36:45,601
We'll take care of it.

721
00:36:45,636 --> 00:36:47,302
I don't need your help.

722
00:36:47,338 --> 00:36:48,403
I'll carry Amaura myself.

723
00:36:54,311 --> 00:36:55,444
[GROANING]

724
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:57,412
[GRUNTING]

725
00:37:01,385 --> 00:37:03,619
Now this big one
will fetch me an even

726
00:37:03,654 --> 00:37:05,521
better price than that Amaura.

727
00:37:05,556 --> 00:37:09,291
A Pokemon hunter.

728
00:37:09,326 --> 00:37:11,460
[POWERING DOWN]

729
00:37:11,495 --> 00:37:12,461
[GASP]

730
00:37:12,496 --> 00:37:14,496
All right,
Pikachu, Thunderbolt!

731
00:37:14,532 --> 00:37:15,430
Pikachu!

732
00:37:19,170 --> 00:37:22,137
I'll fix all of you.

733
00:37:22,173 --> 00:37:23,438
[GROWLING]

734
00:37:46,297 --> 00:37:48,497
[CHIRPING]

735
00:37:48,532 --> 00:37:50,299
What a bad man.

736
00:37:50,334 --> 00:37:52,601
Pokemon hunters
only want one thing--

737
00:37:52,670 --> 00:37:55,337
to make money stealing Pokemon.

738
00:37:55,372 --> 00:37:58,307
So bad things like this--
do they happen a lot?

739
00:37:58,342 --> 00:37:59,408
Yes.

740
00:37:59,443 --> 00:38:02,311
But I can usually drive
them off by creating mist

741
00:38:02,346 --> 00:38:04,146
long before they get this far.

742
00:38:14,592 --> 00:38:15,557
[GASP]

743
00:38:15,593 --> 00:38:16,525
Pika.

744
00:38:21,365 --> 00:38:24,333
VOLCANION: This is
Nebel Plateau, our home.

745
00:38:31,408 --> 00:38:32,574
So many Pokemon!

746
00:38:32,610 --> 00:38:34,509
And they're totally cute!

747
00:38:45,189 --> 00:38:46,455
[BEEPING]

748
00:38:47,191 --> 00:38:48,423
- Drill.
- Pika, pika.

749
00:38:48,459 --> 00:38:49,391
Pika!

750
00:38:49,426 --> 00:38:51,393
Dedenne.

751
00:38:51,428 --> 00:38:52,361
Pika?

752
00:38:52,396 --> 00:38:53,562
Dedenne.

753
00:38:53,597 --> 00:38:56,198
Everybody seems
pretty afraid of us.

754
00:38:56,233 --> 00:38:57,432
You know why.

755
00:38:57,468 --> 00:38:59,234
You're humans, right?

756
00:38:59,270 --> 00:39:02,137
It does look like they
don't trust us at all.

757
00:39:02,172 --> 00:39:03,338
I wonder why that is.

758
00:39:08,512 --> 00:39:09,444
All right.

759
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:11,179
I'll treat Amaura.
Don't worry.

760
00:39:11,215 --> 00:39:12,147
Treat.

761
00:39:12,182 --> 00:39:14,516
Don't just do whatever you want.

762
00:39:14,551 --> 00:39:15,484
Don't be so angry.

763
00:39:15,519 --> 00:39:18,420
You've got to trust
us a little bit.

764
00:39:18,455 --> 00:39:19,388
[BEEPING]

765
00:39:19,423 --> 00:39:21,156
You help, too, Bonnie.
BONNIE: Sure!

766
00:39:21,191 --> 00:39:22,190
CHYMIA: Let me help, too.

767
00:39:22,226 --> 00:39:23,225
I could help, too.

768
00:39:28,565 --> 00:39:30,132
Does it sting?

769
00:39:30,167 --> 00:39:31,199
It'll all be over soon.

770
00:39:31,235 --> 00:39:33,101
You've just got to be strong.

771
00:39:33,137 --> 00:39:33,568
Pika.

772
00:39:39,276 --> 00:39:41,376
CHYMIA: The bandage is freezing.

773
00:39:41,412 --> 00:39:44,346
This sort of thing happens
with ice type Pokemon.

774
00:39:44,381 --> 00:39:46,148
It's proof of the healing.

775
00:39:46,183 --> 00:39:47,482
That means the
medicine's working.

776
00:39:47,518 --> 00:39:49,584
Amaura, that's so great.

777
00:39:49,620 --> 00:39:50,585
Dedenne-ne.

778
00:39:50,621 --> 00:39:52,487
Amaura.

779
00:39:52,523 --> 00:39:54,556
Forget all the bad times.

780
00:39:54,591 --> 00:39:56,591
You're in a safe place now.

781
00:39:56,627 --> 00:39:58,160
You have food here.

782
00:39:58,195 --> 00:39:59,594
You have friends, too.

783
00:39:59,630 --> 00:40:01,530
'Maura.

784
00:40:01,565 --> 00:40:03,131
Sleep now, Amaura.

785
00:40:07,171 --> 00:40:08,370
[BEEPING]

786
00:40:11,508 --> 00:40:15,143
[LULLABY MUSIC PLAYING]

787
00:40:23,520 --> 00:40:24,453
Pika!

788
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:57,486
Pi?

789
00:40:57,521 --> 00:40:58,453
Huh?

790
00:41:01,492 --> 00:41:04,426
Pika?

791
00:41:04,461 --> 00:41:06,128
Pika.

792
00:41:06,163 --> 00:41:08,563
It must be that they're
scared because we're here.

793
00:41:08,599 --> 00:41:12,534
Well, we may be humans, but
Pokemon are still Pokemon.

794
00:41:12,569 --> 00:41:13,535
All right.

795
00:41:13,570 --> 00:41:15,537
Now, everybody out!

796
00:41:20,244 --> 00:41:22,277
Pancha-cha.

797
00:41:22,312 --> 00:41:23,545
Yeah!
Great idea.

798
00:41:23,580 --> 00:41:24,513
I'm in.

799
00:41:27,484 --> 00:41:28,316
Hawlucha.

800
00:41:28,352 --> 00:41:29,551
Talonflame.

801
00:41:29,586 --> 00:41:32,154
Bla, bluh.

802
00:41:32,189 --> 00:41:33,155
Bun!
Bunnelby!

803
00:41:33,190 --> 00:41:33,622
Luxray.

804
00:41:33,657 --> 00:41:34,589
You see?

805
00:41:34,625 --> 00:41:37,159
You don't need to
be afraid of us.

806
00:41:37,194 --> 00:41:40,562
Help us show them
we're friendly.

807
00:41:40,597 --> 00:41:41,530
Pikachu!

808
00:41:47,571 --> 00:41:49,504
Ch-ch-ch cha-cha-chu.

809
00:41:49,540 --> 00:41:50,539
Che.

810
00:41:50,574 --> 00:41:51,473
Eee!

811
00:41:54,578 --> 00:41:55,477
Chu!

812
00:42:01,618 --> 00:42:03,285
Hawlucha.

813
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:05,220
Cha-cha.

814
00:42:05,255 --> 00:42:06,221
Lucha.

815
00:42:06,256 --> 00:42:07,189
Lucha!

816
00:42:07,224 --> 00:42:07,656
Pikachu.

817
00:42:31,648 --> 00:42:33,315
[BEEPING]

818
00:42:33,350 --> 00:42:34,316
Wow, this is great!

819
00:42:34,351 --> 00:42:35,283
Yeah!

820
00:42:37,654 --> 00:42:38,587
Argh.

821
00:42:38,622 --> 00:42:40,522
Huh?

822
00:42:40,557 --> 00:42:42,224
Volcanion, are you OK?

823
00:42:42,259 --> 00:42:45,327
Hey, wait a minute--
the Pokemon hunter.

824
00:42:45,362 --> 00:42:46,595
You need help, too.

825
00:42:46,630 --> 00:42:48,230
I need nothing.

826
00:42:48,265 --> 00:42:51,466
Magearna, stay out of the
flower field for a while, OK?

827
00:42:54,271 --> 00:42:55,470
But what about you?

828
00:42:58,509 --> 00:42:59,341
Hey!

829
00:42:59,376 --> 00:43:00,308
Wait for me!

830
00:43:00,344 --> 00:43:01,276
Bonnie.

831
00:43:13,323 --> 00:43:15,524
ASH: It's a hot spring.

832
00:43:15,559 --> 00:43:17,292
BONNIE: Like a giant bath.

833
00:43:17,327 --> 00:43:20,295
A bath will fix me right up.

834
00:43:20,330 --> 00:43:21,263
Wow.

835
00:43:30,541 --> 00:43:34,309
Quick, Ash, you've got to
get out of there right away.

836
00:43:34,344 --> 00:43:36,177
Wha?

837
00:43:36,213 --> 00:43:37,178
Whoa!

838
00:43:37,214 --> 00:43:40,482
Your suit's
absorbing the water.

839
00:43:40,517 --> 00:43:42,183
[YELLING]

840
00:43:49,226 --> 00:43:50,492
Eugh, and then some.

841
00:43:54,531 --> 00:43:55,463
Hm.

842
00:43:55,499 --> 00:43:57,599
You humans are an
annoying bunch.

843
00:44:07,277 --> 00:44:08,176
Wrench, please.

844
00:44:08,211 --> 00:44:09,578
Bunnelby.

845
00:44:09,613 --> 00:44:11,313
Che.

846
00:44:11,348 --> 00:44:12,280
Thanks a lot.

847
00:44:17,521 --> 00:44:20,221
Working on gadgets
along with Pokemon.

848
00:44:20,257 --> 00:44:23,558
I'm sure it must have been
like this for Nicola, too.

849
00:44:23,594 --> 00:44:26,528
Nicola thought the world
needed both humans and Pokemon

850
00:44:26,563 --> 00:44:29,598
to be in harmony, which I
believe is what inspired

851
00:44:29,633 --> 00:44:32,133
him to create Magearna.

852
00:44:32,169 --> 00:44:34,536
Magearna's the living
embodiment of the philosophy

853
00:44:34,571 --> 00:44:37,272
of arcane science.

854
00:44:37,307 --> 00:44:40,542
At least, that's the way I
prefer to interpret that.

855
00:44:40,577 --> 00:44:42,310
It's such a beautiful idea.

856
00:44:46,550 --> 00:44:49,384
ASH: So you're always here,
watching out for everyone.

857
00:44:49,419 --> 00:44:50,452
Ha.

858
00:44:50,487 --> 00:44:53,521
That's because I never
know when I might explode.

859
00:44:53,557 --> 00:44:55,156
You've got that right.

860
00:44:55,192 --> 00:44:55,957
Pikachu.

861
00:44:55,993 --> 00:44:58,360
Why don't you
two get some sleep.

862
00:44:58,395 --> 00:45:00,595
You're keeping
watch, I am, too.

863
00:45:00,631 --> 00:45:02,564
Pika, Pikachu.

864
00:45:02,633 --> 00:45:04,299
Do as you like.

865
00:45:04,334 --> 00:45:05,367
I will.

866
00:45:05,402 --> 00:45:06,301
Pika-Pika.

867
00:45:15,579 --> 00:45:17,512
[CHUCKLING]

868
00:45:23,153 --> 00:45:25,120
Ta-da!

869
00:45:25,155 --> 00:45:28,089
Your clothes--
they're all clean.

870
00:45:28,125 --> 00:45:29,057
Wow.

871
00:45:29,092 --> 00:45:30,125
Thanks a lot, Serena.

872
00:45:30,160 --> 00:45:31,092
Pikachu!

873
00:45:42,105 --> 00:45:44,873
[BEEPING]

874
00:46:03,026 --> 00:46:04,325
Oh, boy.

875
00:46:04,361 --> 00:46:05,360
This won't be easy.

876
00:46:11,034 --> 00:46:11,966
Gulpin.

877
00:46:12,002 --> 00:46:12,934
Bunnelby.

878
00:46:18,875 --> 00:46:19,307
Yes!

879
00:46:24,314 --> 00:46:25,146
It worked!

880
00:46:40,130 --> 00:46:41,029
BONNIE: Yay!

881
00:46:41,064 --> 00:46:42,997
They brought those
berries for us.

882
00:46:49,339 --> 00:46:50,138
Hm.

883
00:46:50,173 --> 00:46:51,139
Incredible.

884
00:46:51,174 --> 00:46:53,908
I never thought I'd
see humans and Pokemon

885
00:46:53,944 --> 00:46:57,278
getting along together here.

886
00:46:57,314 --> 00:47:00,915
All these Pokemon--
they've been hurt by humans,

887
00:47:00,951 --> 00:47:01,349
haven't they?

888
00:47:01,384 --> 00:47:03,318
Yes, they have.

889
00:47:03,353 --> 00:47:06,087
You, too?

890
00:47:06,123 --> 00:47:07,956
Don't worry about
what happened to me.

891
00:47:14,931 --> 00:47:15,864
All fixed!

892
00:47:15,899 --> 00:47:16,865
Good as new.

893
00:47:16,900 --> 00:47:19,267
Next time, we're going
to be working on you.

894
00:47:19,302 --> 00:47:20,268
Working on us?

895
00:47:20,303 --> 00:47:21,136
Pika?

896
00:47:24,875 --> 00:47:26,074
Watch what this one can do.

897
00:47:38,889 --> 00:47:40,021
It's about time.

898
00:47:40,056 --> 00:47:42,056
It worked!

899
00:47:42,092 --> 00:47:43,091
Thanks so much, Gulpin.

900
00:47:50,000 --> 00:47:50,899
Huh?

901
00:47:50,934 --> 00:47:51,900
Pika?

902
00:47:51,935 --> 00:47:54,135
This Gulpin has its reasons.

903
00:47:54,171 --> 00:47:56,104
Anyway, the bands are gone.

904
00:47:56,139 --> 00:47:58,106
Leave.

905
00:47:58,141 --> 00:48:00,341
Even after all
that's happened?

906
00:48:00,377 --> 00:48:03,144
After everybody's starting
to get along so well?

907
00:48:03,180 --> 00:48:04,879
Doesn't mean anything.

908
00:48:04,915 --> 00:48:05,980
It does, too.

909
00:48:06,016 --> 00:48:08,016
You only did that because
we were stuck together.

910
00:48:08,051 --> 00:48:10,151
Hey, I really like Pokemon.

911
00:48:10,187 --> 00:48:12,086
I want to protect them, too.

912
00:48:12,122 --> 00:48:14,022
If you're going to
be a Pokemon trainer,

913
00:48:14,057 --> 00:48:17,058
then you've got to learn how
to make Pokemon feel safe.

914
00:48:17,093 --> 00:48:20,295
Right, buddy?
- Pika, pika!

915
00:48:20,330 --> 00:48:23,865
Spare me your pretty
words or I'll blast you.

916
00:48:23,900 --> 00:48:24,999
You try it!

917
00:48:25,035 --> 00:48:27,001
Pika!

918
00:48:27,037 --> 00:48:27,969
Bunnelby.

919
00:48:39,149 --> 00:48:40,882
I'm going to sleep.

920
00:48:40,917 --> 00:48:41,850
Aw.

921
00:49:19,256 --> 00:49:20,188
What?

922
00:49:20,223 --> 00:49:22,123
I brought Poke Puffs.

923
00:49:22,158 --> 00:49:24,092
Serena and Chymia made them.

924
00:49:24,127 --> 00:49:25,026
Pika.

925
00:49:25,061 --> 00:49:27,228
Huh?

926
00:49:27,264 --> 00:49:29,931
You were surprised
back there, weren't you?

927
00:49:29,966 --> 00:49:31,232
They just didn't understand.

928
00:49:31,268 --> 00:49:35,069
Please forgive them.

929
00:49:35,105 --> 00:49:36,070
Sorry, Gulpin.

930
00:49:36,106 --> 00:49:37,038
Pikachu.

931
00:49:42,913 --> 00:49:44,178
This little one
came here after being

932
00:49:44,214 --> 00:49:47,849
abandoned by its trainer.

933
00:49:47,884 --> 00:49:49,017
Pika.

934
00:49:49,052 --> 00:49:52,153
I don't know if anything
happened before that.

935
00:49:52,188 --> 00:49:55,223
He doesn't tell me,
and I don't ask.

936
00:49:55,258 --> 00:49:59,193
The only thing I know is that,
right before its trainer left,

937
00:49:59,229 --> 00:50:01,930
he gave Gulpin a big hug.

938
00:50:08,004 --> 00:50:11,973
All of the Pokemon here have
been wounded by the selfishness

939
00:50:12,008 --> 00:50:13,975
and lies of humans.

940
00:50:14,010 --> 00:50:20,181
They may be laughing now, but
their wounds are deeply-rooted.

941
00:50:20,216 --> 00:50:24,919
And that's the reason
I can't trust humans.

942
00:50:24,955 --> 00:50:29,123
Pokemon are incapable of
lying, but humans are.

943
00:50:29,159 --> 00:50:31,192
And do.

944
00:50:31,227 --> 00:50:32,160
Pika pika.

945
00:50:32,195 --> 00:50:33,127
Pika.

946
00:50:33,163 --> 00:50:34,095
Pika pi.

947
00:50:34,130 --> 00:50:35,063
Really?

948
00:50:35,098 --> 00:50:36,931
This one doesn't lie?

949
00:50:36,967 --> 00:50:37,899
Pika!

950
00:50:37,934 --> 00:50:38,967
Pikachu!

951
00:50:39,002 --> 00:50:40,168
Pikachu.

952
00:50:40,203 --> 00:50:44,973
He fights with all he has
to protect the ones he loves.

953
00:50:45,008 --> 00:50:45,974
Pika pika.

954
00:50:46,009 --> 00:50:47,141
Thank you for that.

955
00:50:47,177 --> 00:50:48,109
You're right.

956
00:50:48,144 --> 00:50:49,344
Pikachu!

957
00:50:49,379 --> 00:50:53,247
Both of you are spewing
nothing but flowery sentiments.

958
00:50:53,283 --> 00:50:55,183
I'm sorry.

959
00:50:55,218 --> 00:50:58,953
Before the others get used
to you, I want you to leave,

960
00:50:58,989 --> 00:51:01,089
though I'm very grateful
to you for what you

961
00:51:01,124 --> 00:51:03,057
did for Magearna and Amaura.

962
00:51:07,998 --> 00:51:09,197
Here.
Go ahead and eat.

963
00:51:19,109 --> 00:51:21,042
Not bad.

964
00:51:21,077 --> 00:51:23,978
If you like it, then why
don't you say you like it?

965
00:51:24,014 --> 00:51:24,946
Pikachu.

966
00:51:24,981 --> 00:51:25,346
Eat.

967
00:51:25,382 --> 00:51:26,314
Both of you.

968
00:51:32,155 --> 00:51:33,154
[RUSTLING]
- Pi?

969
00:51:33,189 --> 00:51:34,088
Pika?

970
00:51:39,996 --> 00:51:42,030
What is that?

971
00:51:42,065 --> 00:51:43,197
[GROWLING]

972
00:51:43,266 --> 00:51:45,933
[ALL SQUEAKING]

973
00:51:51,274 --> 00:51:53,141
[GRUNTING]

974
00:51:57,147 --> 00:51:59,313
[GRUNTING]

975
00:51:59,349 --> 00:52:02,016
[ALL PANTING]

976
00:52:07,357 --> 00:52:10,058
[ALL SCREAMING]

977
00:52:15,065 --> 00:52:16,030
[ALL GASPING]

978
00:52:16,066 --> 00:52:17,965
[GROANING]

979
00:52:19,102 --> 00:52:21,069
Grexit, Talonflame!

980
00:52:21,104 --> 00:52:22,270
Luxray, Greninja!

981
00:52:22,305 --> 00:52:25,239
Woo!

982
00:52:25,275 --> 00:52:28,009
[ALL SHOUTING]

983
00:52:29,012 --> 00:52:32,146
[HOWLING]

984
00:52:32,182 --> 00:52:33,314
Everyone!

985
00:52:33,349 --> 00:52:35,116
[GASPS]

986
00:52:35,151 --> 00:52:37,185
Kanu!

987
00:52:37,220 --> 00:52:39,020
Dreberon.

988
00:52:39,055 --> 00:52:40,988
Jiyoo!

989
00:52:41,024 --> 00:52:42,156
[ALL SCREAMING]

990
00:52:42,192 --> 00:52:47,128
[GRUNTING]

991
00:52:47,163 --> 00:52:48,129
Huh?

992
00:52:48,164 --> 00:52:49,097
Huh?

993
00:52:49,132 --> 00:52:51,265
[ALL EXCLAIMING]

994
00:52:54,237 --> 00:52:55,136
You two.

995
00:52:58,108 --> 00:52:59,974
Well, well.

996
00:53:00,009 --> 00:53:00,975
[CLICK]

997
00:53:01,010 --> 00:53:03,111
[ALL MOANING]

998
00:53:06,316 --> 00:53:07,281
If you resist--

999
00:53:07,317 --> 00:53:08,182
[CLICK]

1000
00:53:08,218 --> 00:53:10,151
[ALL MOANING]

1001
00:53:14,324 --> 00:53:15,289
You're the worst.

1002
00:53:15,325 --> 00:53:16,224
Bega!

1003
00:53:16,259 --> 00:53:18,092
They're humans.

1004
00:53:18,128 --> 00:53:21,162
They think nothing of
the lives of Pokemon.

1005
00:53:21,197 --> 00:53:22,263
Hey!

1006
00:53:22,298 --> 00:53:23,998
I'll blast you!

1007
00:53:24,033 --> 00:53:25,199
Manectric, electrotrain!

1008
00:53:25,235 --> 00:53:28,102
Steelix, use stealth rocket.

1009
00:53:28,171 --> 00:53:30,972
Mey, nethra.

1010
00:53:31,007 --> 00:53:32,974
[SCREAMING]

1011
00:53:33,009 --> 00:53:34,142
[GASPING]

1012
00:53:34,177 --> 00:53:37,145
[GROWLING]

1013
00:53:37,180 --> 00:53:39,147
How dare you?

1014
00:53:43,119 --> 00:53:44,285
[SQUEAKING]

1015
00:53:44,320 --> 00:53:49,023
If you want to help them,
then you should come with us.

1016
00:53:49,058 --> 00:53:52,293
If you do, then
everybody is happy.

1017
00:53:52,328 --> 00:53:54,061
No!

1018
00:53:54,097 --> 00:53:55,096
Don't go, Magearna.

1019
00:53:55,131 --> 00:53:56,197
[GROWLING]

1020
00:53:56,232 --> 00:53:57,999
Then I've no choice.

1021
00:53:58,034 --> 00:53:58,966
[CLICK]

1022
00:53:59,002 --> 00:54:02,003
[ALL SCREAMING]

1023
00:54:02,038 --> 00:54:04,205
Oh, you'll pay for this!

1024
00:54:04,240 --> 00:54:07,008
Oh!

1025
00:54:07,043 --> 00:54:09,143
[BEEPING]

1026
00:54:12,348 --> 00:54:15,149
[GASPS] Magearna!

1027
00:54:15,185 --> 00:54:16,117
Heeda.

1028
00:54:20,290 --> 00:54:22,123
So now you understand.

1029
00:54:22,158 --> 00:54:23,291
[LAUGHS]

1030
00:54:23,326 --> 00:54:25,193
Use psychic.

1031
00:54:25,228 --> 00:54:26,294
Zob.

1032
00:54:26,329 --> 00:54:27,328
Oog nay.

1033
00:54:32,202 --> 00:54:33,167
Googi.

1034
00:54:33,203 --> 00:54:35,069
Magearna!

1035
00:54:35,104 --> 00:54:36,037
Ah.

1036
00:54:42,345 --> 00:54:44,078
[ALL GASPING]

1037
00:54:44,113 --> 00:54:45,279
[PANTING]

1038
00:54:50,119 --> 00:54:53,087
[GROWLING]

1039
00:54:53,122 --> 00:54:55,022
[BEEPING]

1040
00:54:55,391 --> 00:54:58,259
Rollie, Alva.

1041
00:54:58,294 --> 00:55:00,094
Everything's OK.

1042
00:55:00,129 --> 00:55:01,329
All of this is for our kingdom.

1043
00:55:01,364 --> 00:55:03,130
[CHUCKLES]

1044
00:55:03,166 --> 00:55:04,298
[SCOFFS]

1045
00:55:04,334 --> 00:55:07,268
[ROARS]

1046
00:55:07,303 --> 00:55:08,302
Oh.

1047
00:55:08,338 --> 00:55:11,138
Alva, why don't we
tell them everything,

1048
00:55:11,207 --> 00:55:14,141
What an incredible creation
Magearna really is?

1049
00:55:14,177 --> 00:55:15,076
Fine.

1050
00:55:15,111 --> 00:55:16,210
Gengar, mean look.

1051
00:55:16,246 --> 00:55:18,179
Gah.

1052
00:55:18,214 --> 00:55:19,180
[BEEPING]

1053
00:55:19,215 --> 00:55:20,147
Huh?

1054
00:55:20,183 --> 00:55:21,148
Ah.

1055
00:55:21,184 --> 00:55:23,317
[BEEPING]

1056
00:55:24,153 --> 00:55:25,086
Gah.

1057
00:55:28,224 --> 00:55:30,258
- [EVIL LAUGH]
- Wait a minute.

1058
00:55:30,293 --> 00:55:33,060
You don't have to
remove its soul-heart.

1059
00:55:33,096 --> 00:55:36,063
That's just as long as
Magearna becomes a spear.

1060
00:55:36,099 --> 00:55:38,099
Nicholas said that-- ah!

1061
00:55:38,134 --> 00:55:40,868
All that I really
need is its soul-heart.

1062
00:55:40,903 --> 00:55:41,435
You can't!

1063
00:55:41,471 --> 00:55:43,337
If you remove it, then--

1064
00:55:49,145 --> 00:55:51,312
[CHUCKLES]

1065
00:55:55,318 --> 00:55:57,318
Alva, what happened?

1066
00:55:57,353 --> 00:55:58,286
It's gone.

1067
00:55:58,321 --> 00:55:59,353
[GASPS]

1068
00:55:59,389 --> 00:56:02,223
Gengar, kindly
return Magearna.

1069
00:56:02,258 --> 00:56:04,292
[SNARLS]

1070
00:56:08,064 --> 00:56:08,996
[GASPS]

1071
00:56:09,032 --> 00:56:11,132
[SHOUTING]

1072
00:56:11,167 --> 00:56:15,870
Chymia, your presence is
not required for my plan.

1073
00:56:15,905 --> 00:56:17,138
Farewell.

1074
00:56:17,173 --> 00:56:18,839
Use hyperbeam.

1075
00:56:18,875 --> 00:56:20,841
[SHOUTING]

1076
00:56:27,183 --> 00:56:29,083
How could you lie to me?

1077
00:56:29,118 --> 00:56:31,052
It wasn't for the kingdom!

1078
00:56:31,087 --> 00:56:35,256
Yes, it was all done for the
glory of the Kingdom of Azoth,

1079
00:56:35,291 --> 00:56:37,892
my ideal one, of course.

1080
00:56:37,927 --> 00:56:39,260
[GASPS]

1081
00:56:39,295 --> 00:56:41,128
Gengar, hypnosis.

1082
00:56:41,164 --> 00:56:43,998
[SNARLING]

1083
00:57:08,041 --> 00:57:10,875
They used dig and safeguard.

1084
00:57:10,910 --> 00:57:12,009
Thank you, everyone.

1085
00:57:12,045 --> 00:57:14,045
Re pow.

1086
00:57:14,080 --> 00:57:15,012
Magearna!

1087
00:57:25,725 --> 00:57:27,992
[ALL EXCLAIMING]

1088
00:57:48,714 --> 00:57:49,880
Volcanion.

1089
00:57:49,916 --> 00:57:50,848
Weepa.

1090
00:57:58,057 --> 00:57:59,924
If it's soul-heart
is returned,

1091
00:57:59,959 --> 00:58:01,926
Magearna should be revived.

1092
00:58:01,961 --> 00:58:02,893
[GASPING]

1093
00:58:06,065 --> 00:58:07,064
Everyone on board.

1094
00:58:10,703 --> 00:58:14,004
Prince Raleigh, I thought
that you would understand,

1095
00:58:14,040 --> 00:58:15,940
that you would be
able to comprehend

1096
00:58:15,975 --> 00:58:17,975
my noblest of dreams.

1097
00:58:18,010 --> 00:58:20,878
There's no reason to
make such a big fuss.

1098
00:58:20,913 --> 00:58:22,847
We're only talking
about one Pokemon.

1099
00:58:31,023 --> 00:58:34,625
[GASPS] It's Magearna.

1100
00:58:34,660 --> 00:58:36,927
I can sense it right from here.

1101
00:58:36,963 --> 00:58:37,895
Oh, Magearna.

1102
00:58:37,930 --> 00:58:39,930
It's crying.

1103
00:58:39,966 --> 00:58:42,900
In that case, it's
retrieved the soul-heart.

1104
00:58:42,935 --> 00:58:44,969
[INAUDIBLE]

1105
00:58:45,004 --> 00:58:46,937
Gengar, psychic.

1106
00:58:46,973 --> 00:58:48,639
Gah!

1107
00:58:48,674 --> 00:58:51,108
You're even less
than useless to me.

1108
00:58:51,144 --> 00:58:52,943
[ALL MOANING]

1109
00:58:52,979 --> 00:58:55,913
[SCREAMING]

1110
00:59:09,662 --> 00:59:11,729
VOLCANION: That
field of flowers,

1111
00:59:11,764 --> 00:59:15,666
that's where I met Magearna
for the very first time.

1112
00:59:15,701 --> 00:59:17,935
Wasn't it 500 years ago?

1113
00:59:17,970 --> 00:59:20,905
I don't know how you
humans measure time.

1114
00:59:20,940 --> 00:59:23,040
But it's a story from
the ancient past.

1115
00:59:38,090 --> 00:59:41,091
Then, as now, the
plateaus. was my home,

1116
00:59:41,127 --> 00:59:44,995
and that of many, many
other troubled Pokemon.

1117
00:59:45,031 --> 00:59:48,999
Oftentimes, I would check the
area for Pokemon that were lost

1118
00:59:49,035 --> 00:59:50,968
and had collapsed
from exhaustion.

1119
01:00:09,689 --> 01:00:11,755
Magearna was the first
one I met that wasn't

1120
01:00:11,791 --> 01:00:13,991
